<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="448" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1445,1723]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1777" box="[151,317,1483,1507]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Ophidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mastacembelus">
<emphasis box="[151,317,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">Mastacembelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Gronow" authorityName="Gronow" authorityYear="1854" box="[325,510,1484,1508]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Mastacembalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="syriacus">
<emphasis box="[325,414,1484,1507]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">syriacus</emphasis>
Gronow
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<bibRefCitation author="Gray, J. E." box="[551,726,1483,1508]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref3258" refString="Gray, J. E. (1854) Catalogue of fish collected and described by Laurence Theodore Gronow, now in the British Museum. British Museum, London, 196 pp. https: // archive. org / details / cataloguefishco 00 graygoog" type="book" year="1854">Gray, 1854: 172</bibRefCitation>
is based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Gronovius, L. T. &amp; Zoophylacii Gronoviani" box="[863,1049,1483,1507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref3304" refString="Gronovius, L. T. (1763 - 1764) Zoophylacii Gronoviani fasciculus primus exhibens animalia quadrupeda, amphibia atque pisces, quae in museo suo adservat, rite examinavit, systematice disposuit, descripsit atque iconibus illustravit Laur. Theod. Gronovius. Vol. 1 (1763) &amp; Vol. 2 (1764). Sumptibus auctoris [published by author], Lugduni Batavorum [Leiden], pp. 1 - 140, pls. 1 - 17 &amp; pp. 141 - 236. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 50229513]" type="url" year="1763">Gronovius (1763</bibRefCitation>
: n. 402, «pl. 5 fig. 1, 2»). The plate is actually pl. 8a. The text [n. 402] includes a reference to 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, A." box="[783,943,1519,1543]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref3831" refString="Russell, A. (1756) The natural history of Aleppo, and parts adjacents. Containing a description of the city, and the principal natural productions in its neighbourhood; together with an account of the climate, inhabitants, and diseases particularly of the plague, with the methods used by the Europeans for their preservation. Millar, London, viii + 266 + 10 pp., 16 pls. [Publication year on title page erroneously as 1856, https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 25600529] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 36635" type="book" year="1756">Russell (1756)</bibRefCitation>
. I designate here the specimen model of plate 12 figure 
<quantity box="[256,297,1555,1580]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, A." box="[336,493,1555,1579]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref3831" refString="Russell, A. (1756) The natural history of Aleppo, and parts adjacents. Containing a description of the city, and the principal natural productions in its neighbourhood; together with an account of the climate, inhabitants, and diseases particularly of the plague, with the methods used by the Europeans for their preservation. Millar, London, viii + 266 + 10 pp., 16 pls. [Publication year on title page erroneously as 1856, https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 25600529] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 36635" type="book" year="1756">Russell (1756)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<typeStatus box="[529,627,1555,1579]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">lectotype</typeStatus>
and this makes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gronow" authorityYear="1854" box="[801,926,1556,1579]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Mastacembalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="syriacus">
<emphasis box="[801,926,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">M. syriacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior objective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walbaum" authorityYear="1792" box="[1262,1369,1555,1579]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mastacembelidae" genus="Ophidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Synbranchiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simack">
<emphasis box="[1262,1369,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">O. simack</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gray, J. E." pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refId="ref3258" refString="Gray, J. E. (1854) Catalogue of fish collected and described by Laurence Theodore Gronow, now in the British Museum. British Museum, London, 196 pp. https: // archive. org / details / cataloguefishco 00 graygoog" type="book" year="1854">Gray (1854)</bibRefCitation>
is a catalogue of Gronow’s collection edited and published by Gray, in which Gronow had added binominal names (
<bibRefCitation author="Wheeler, A." box="[158,320,1627,1651]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" pagination="187 - 249" refId="ref5329" refString="Wheeler, A. (1958) The Gronovious fish collection: a catalogue and historical account. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Historical Series, 1, 187 - 249, pls. 26 - 34. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 2238853]" type="journal article" year="1958">Wheeler, 1958</bibRefCitation>
). Gronovius’ specimen is not mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation author="Wheeler, A." box="[786,973,1627,1651]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" pagination="187 - 249" refId="ref5329" refString="Wheeler, A. (1958) The Gronovious fish collection: a catalogue and historical account. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Historical Series, 1, 187 - 249, pls. 26 - 34. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 2238853]" type="journal article" year="1958">Wheeler’s (1958)</bibRefCitation>
catalogue of the Gronovius fish collection. Wheeler mentioned only fish preserved as dried skins of half fishes on sheets of paper; the specimen received from A. Russell was possibly not a ‘herbarium’ specimen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
